  <static seed="54" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring100.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{9x^{5}y^{5}-18x^{4}y^{5}+15x^{3}y^{5}}=</m> <fillin characters="31" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>3x^{3}y^{5}\mathopen{}\left(3x^{2}-6x+5\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The greatest common factor is <m>3x^3y^{5}</m>, so we can factor the polynomial as follows:</p>
<p><m>{9x^{5}y^{5}-18x^{4}y^{5}+15x^{3}y^{5}}={3x^{3}y^{5}\mathopen{}\left(3x^{2}-6x+5\right)}</m></p>
</solution>
